<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880318-0079 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Avnet Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AVT </CO><TEXT>   Avnet Inc.'s net income for the year ending June 30 will more than double the $22.8 million, or 64 cents a share, of fiscal 1987, Lee Machiz, president, told securities analysts in New York.    The New York-based electronics distributor's sales will grow at least 17% to more than $1.8 billion from $1.54 billion, Mr. Machiz said.    For fiscal 1989, the executive added, sales are expected to top $2 billion, and earnings again will increase; he wasn't more specific.    Avnet's shares rose 87.5 cents, to $26.375, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday. </TEXT></DOC>